      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Organized in Portsmouth, Virginia in 1843 by
         African-American members of the Dinwiddie Street Methodist
         Church who wanted their own church.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>The Quarterly Conference Minutes, 27 December 1842-31
         December 1856, of the Monumental Methodist Church, Portsmouth,
         Virginia (previously known as the Dinwiddie Street Methodist
         Church), includes reports from the African Methodist
         Church.</p>
